int32 rtk_SetQoSConfig ( int  chid,
int  sid,
SessionType  type,
TstQosCfg *  cfg 
)

Set QoS configuration.

Invoke rtk_SetQoSConfig() after creating a RTP session or modifying RTP parameters.

Parameters
chidThe channel number.
sidThe session number. Usually 0 for master session, 1 for slave(conference) session.
typeThe Session Type (session_type_rtp/session_type_rtcp/session_type_t38)
cfgThe QoS configuration for dscpRemark vlanPriorityRemark quenuNum
Return values
0Success

Parameters
